Prey: Insects, slugs, worms, arachnids, and snails
Fun Fact: The wood frog lives the furthest north of any other North American amphibian including in the Arctic Circle.
Estimated Population Size: While there are no estimates of the global population size, the overall population is stable.
Biggest Threat: Habitat fragmentation and loss due to anthropogenic causes and natural changes in habitat.
Litter Size: Females typically lay between 1,000 and 3,000 eggs.
Predators: Larger frogs, snakes, raccoons, herons, skunks, and mink.
Location: North America, into the Arctic Circle and the Southern U.S.
Name: Wood Frog
